onseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Restrict students to observation only","Allow students to work independently to build confidence","Transfer supervision responsibility to junior doctors","Encourage students to perform any task requested by other staff","Clearly define permitted activities and level of supervision required"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that supervisors must \u003Cstrong\u003Eclearly define permitted activities and level of supervision required\u003C/strong\u003E. This ensures patient safety while maximising appropriate learning opportunities. Supervisors must explicitly communicate what tasks students can perform and what level of supervision is needed for each activity.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAllow students to work independently to build confidence\u003C/strong\u003E - This compromises patient safety and exceeds appropriate scope of practice for students\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEncourage students to perform any task requested by other staff\u003C/strong\u003E - This may lead to students performing tasks beyond their competence level\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERestrict students to observation only\u003C/strong\u003E - This is overly restrictive and prevents appropriate hands-on learning opportunities\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETransfer supervision responsibility to junior doctors\u003C/strong\u003E - The primary supervisor maintains overall responsibility for student supervision\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EMedical students must only perform tasks within their competence level and under appropriate supervision. The supervisor is responsible for ensuring both patient safety and educational value while gradually expanding the student\u0027s capabilities.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical supervisors must clearly define the scope of practice and limitations for medical students under their supervision.","Medical students must only perform tasks within their level of competence and under appropriate supervision.","Supervisors are responsible for ensuring patient safety while facilitating student learning opportunities."],"references":["DeWitt DE. Incorporating medical students into your practice. Aust Fam Physician. 2006 Jan-Feb;35(1-2):24-6. PMID: 16489381. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16489381/","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65849"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18950"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65849","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65849"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-21T15:04:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-21T15:04:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11684"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80558"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{